 preventing excessive melting. This is supported by the evidence that shows that for both low and high laser powers, there are clear thresholds below which lack of fusion become predominant, but no clear threshold for keyhole mode porosity formation. The results also indicate that higher power and speed allow a wider \\\"safe\\\" process parameter range with less extensive keyhole mode porosity, as the higher speed suppresses instability in the vapor depression. Additionally, a smaller scan spacing can result in too much overlap, causing longer fabrication times and limiting the maximum layer height that can be used. A larger scan spacing can help avoid improper melting of particles and reduce the risk of balling and dimensional inaccuracy.\"\n        ],\n        \"semantic_type\": \"\",\n        \"description\": \"\"\n      }\n    }\n  ]\n}"}},"metadata":{},"execution_count":17}]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["## Evaluation Summary\n","##This provides an overall summary of retrieval performance and latency across the benchmark questions.\n","\n","df = evaluate_graph_rag(graph_rag_qa, benchmark, k=5)\n","\n","print(df[[\n","    \"retrieval_accuracy\",\n","    \"defect_label_precision\",\n","    \"defect_label_recall\",\n","    \"latency\"\n","]].mean())\n","\n","print(df[\"parameter_accuracy\"].dropna().mean())"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"YYhii5qimvZw","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1774652909019,"user_tz":0,"elapsed":64165,"user":{"displayName":"Muhammad Awan","userId":"05534583974233650953"}},"outputId":"76058eb8-9110-4554-c474-c0087ce600bd"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stderr","text":["Setting `pad_token_id` to `eos_token_id`:2 for open-end generation.\n"]},{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Matched graph nodes: ['laser power', 'keyhole']\n","\n","=== Retrieved Evidence ===\n","final_cleaned_40_chunk_2 | defects: ['porosity', 'keyhole']\n","final_cleaned_16_chu